content:
Estimated Examples:
Example 1:
Text: <url>, whom you indefblocked almost a year ago, is requesting another chance and seems penitent. Have you any comments?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 2:
Text: Thank you for taking the time to dig up the references. Are you planning on integrating them into the article sometime soon?
Annotation from annotator: 20

Example 3:
Text: Hi! How u find out my article:)?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 4:
Text: While watching the contribs I noticed that the bot blanked <url> which has already been checked and is listed at <url>. Isn't that supposed to be the thing that these lists of MRGs were supposed to prevent?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 5:
Text: I noticed you delinked 1993 in the MGM Grand Las Vegas article <url>.  What is MoS?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 6:
Text: I wouldn't know where to put it. I know Record Charts is for charts etc and the certifications but where would I put a discography question?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 7:
Text: I am not sure why <url> is not just in the article <url> as a straight table. Is there some chance the template might be used on another article?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 8:
Text: I noticed you have improved the "human rights" section on the article <url>. Could you update the main article: <url>?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 9:
Text: ---- Though I thought I would note that you have now exceeded <big>'''500'''</big> edits while on "wikibreak" and that is over less than 10 days, May I ask what kind of break is that???
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 10:
Text: Hi.. I'd actually like to move all images in <url> to the Commons.  Is there a way that I can do it myself?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 11:
Text: Yeah, at the moment. Unless there are any other dryandras on the cusp of GA-hood....?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 12:
Text: You also did three reversions. Where are the administrators, meanwhile?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 13:
Text: hi Mustafaa I have some historical pictures and some sentences written on them which seems to be arabic. Can you tell me if it is arabic or not if i send you a copy?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 14:
Text: Hi! Could you consider speedy deleting <url>?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 15:
Text: I'm afraid I don't understand what you are asking. Could you perhaps try to explain it in another way?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 16:
Text: Name's don't change. I'm going to have say, that his name is to be kept in the article however what about creating a page about Harry Potter characters in fanfiction or something like that?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 17:
Text: About the arrow pawn: it moves one square per turn (if it's not Persson's variant), right? When it moves two squares in the Persson variant, can it jump?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 18:
Text: Stephan, I am Deborah Byrd, producer of the Earth & Sky radio series, and I'm looking for a reference for this statement of yours on the discussion page of the article about scientists who oppose the mainstream view of global warming (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientists_opposing_the_mainstream_scientific_assessment_of_global_warming) "We are not talking 51% or 60% or 75%, but rather 95%+ (or "near unanimity in the peer reviewed published literature and in official statements by professional scientific organisations"). --Stephan Schulz 08:26, 18 November 2006 (UTC)"  How did you determine that there is 95% agreement in the peer reviewed published literature and in official statements by professional scientific organizations?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 19:
Text: Okay, so yeah, it's possible that that's his intent, but I even if it were, I don't see why the file has less value. Are interviews with BLP subjects not considered valid EL's general?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 20:
Text: While editing the COIN page regarding Ciplex, I accidently broke your sig. Since I don't want any more flame, could you please fix it?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 21:
Text: Thanks for your support! Would you consider commenting on the <url> talk page, saying it has your support (and adding those comments for discussion)?
Annotation from annotator: 20

Example 22:
Text: I like yours better, it's less demeaning. This is pretty new to me... should I remove it or leave it?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 23:
Text: You said that the Category: "Songs Performed on 'Make Your Own Kind Of Music'" might be deleted. Could you explain your reasoning?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 24:
Text: In instances where there is one major usage of a name and several smaller ones it is conventional to leave the major one in the namespace and have a link in the top to the others (or to <url>. Surely 99.9% of people interested in <url> are going to be looking for the main one, so wouldn't it have made more sense to have left it there rather than making it a redirect?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 25:
Text: I have noticed that your objection to someone who unilaterally stops a straw poll. What, then, do you think of somebody who unilaterally ''starts'' a straw poll?
Annotation from annotator: 8

Example 26:
Text: <url> Is there any way I can convince you to change your mind?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 27:
Text: Just reminder, but you tagged <url> with the GAreview tag several days ago. Have you completed your review comments yet?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 28:
Text: Good! By the way, what do you think of merging the recurring animals in <url> to <url> and then getting rid of the rest?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Example 29:
Text: Done. I may have missed a few links when copying them across, so could you please look through it just in case?
Annotation from annotator: 20

Example 30:
Text: I noticed that (although it's striked through now), you considered opposing <url>'s adminship bid on the grounds that they suffer from auditory hallucinations. For future consideration, may I point you <url>?
Annotation from annotator: 16

Target Example:
Text: Is <url> what you're referring to??  '''''One''''' autograph page that he deleted almost '''''five months''''' ago and you're now attacking him as if he deleted every single autograph book ever?
Annotation from annotator:
